:"1065–1118","1091–1138":"1091–1138","1115–1167":"1115–1167","1020–1064":"1020–1064","1030–Female":"1030–Overleden","1091":"1091","about 1091":"circa 1091","1065":"1065","1064":"1064","1020":"1020","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","1118":"1118","Abt 1064":"circa 1064","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1167":"1167","about 1115":"circa 1115","Abt 1050":"circa 1050","about 1130":"circa 1130","Waldfeucht, Landkreis Heinsberg, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Waldfeucht, Heinsberg, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland","Zutphen, Gelderland, Netherlands":"Zutphen, Gelderland, Nederland","Germany":"Duitsland"},"en":{"Abt 1050–about 1130":"about 1050–about 1130","1050–1130":"1050–1130","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1065–1118":"1065–1118","1091–1138":"1091–1138","1115–1167":"1115–1167","1020–1064":"1020–1064","1030–Female":"1030–Deceased","1091":"1091","about 1091":"about 1091","1065":"1065","1064":"1064","1020":"1020","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","1118":"1118","Abt 1064":"about 1064","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1167":"1167","about 1115":"about 1115","Abt 1050":"about 1050","about 1130":"about 1130","Waldfeucht, Landkreis Heinsberg, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Waldfeucht, Heinsberg, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany","Zutphen, Gelderland, Netherlands":"Zutphen, Gelderland, Netherlands","Germany":"Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Zutphen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Sutphin  , a surname of Dutch origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Sutphin","meanings":["Americanized form of Dutch <b>Van Zutphen</b>: habitational name for someone from Zutphen in the province of Gelderland. Compare   Sutfin   and   Sutphen  ."]}]},{"name":"Otto","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a short form of any of the various Germanic compound personal names containing the element <i>od</i>, <i>ot</i> ‘prosperity, wealth’ (  compare the corresponding Old English <i>ēad</i> in names such as  Edward   and   Edwin  ).  St Otto of Bamberg  (  d. 1139 ) was a missionary to the Pomeranians.  Otto the Great  (  912–73 ) is generally regarded as the founder of the Holy Roman Empire, and the name has been borne by several members of German and Austrian royal houses. It was recorded occasionally among immigrants to England from the Low Countries in the 14th century, but failed to establish itself. Since the 19th century it has again been used occasionally in the English-speaking world, mostly among immigrants from Germanic countries."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Otto von Zutphen was born about 1050, his father, Gottschalk VON ZÜTPHEN, was 32 and his mother, Adelheid von Braunweiler, was 22. He had at least 2 daughters with Judith von Arnstein. He died about 1130, at the age of 82, and was buried in Waldfeucht, Heinsberg, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany."},"et":{"Abt 1050–about 1130":"umbes 1050–umbes 1130","1050–1130":"1050–1130","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1065–1118":"1065–1118","1091–1138":"1091–1138","1115–1167":"1115–1167","1020–1064":"1020–1064","1030–Female":"1030–Surnud","1091":"1091","about 1091":"umbes 1091","1065":"1065","1064":"1064","1020":"1020","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","1118":"1118","Abt 1064":"umbes 1064","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1167":"1167","about 1115":"umbes 1115","Abt 1050":"umbes 1050","about 1130":"umbes 1130